Faithful nonzero exit (215 §3 strain-and-exit, tc-exec-nonzero-exit closed): this is a
`set -e; dpkg -s nginx && { … }` book whose guard FAILS (nginx absent, rc 1). The `&&`
short-circuits the dead block; the AND-OR list's rc is the failed left's, so the script
exits 1 WITHOUT aborting (dash: `set -e; false && {…}` exits 1, prints no error). The bare
book exits 1 identically, so the apply artifact (`false && { :; :; }`) is FAITHFUL. Without
this marker the exec gate treats the nonzero exit as "errored when run" and false-fails;
with it the gate asserts rc == 1 exactly and the empty run-set is exec-verified (was
analysis-only before slice-1). The value lives in the filename; this text is documentation.
